job application for marketing research & intelligence analyst at element ai





















          apply now

marketing research & intelligence analyst

        at element ai

(view all jobs)

        montreal



we are rapidly growing our intelligence team in montreal, and are especially excited to meet candidates who are driven to understand and share knowledge. as an analyst, your main responsibility will be to understand the intelligence needs of the groups you will be working with, with the help of the team, find the information needed and do the analytical work needed to make the information actionable.
what you will be doing: 

identify, research, collect, organize and summarize market intelligence & research in order to support element ai’s key strategic objectives by monitoring the rapidly evolving best practices and impacts in the commercial and emerging ai industry. including but not withstanding consumer, competitive, market, economic, industry specific, financial, social, political, and operational intelligence; 
translate data and information obtained into concise, effective and articulate summary reports with relevant highlight/soundbites for various internal or external client groups;
ensure the timely distribution of relevant aggregated intelligence with appropriate groups and individuals as requested; 
identify and ensuring alignment of research efforts with qualitative return on investment against our key strategic objectives with smart key performance indicators (kpis/okrs);
track and stay within the limits of allocated resources including budgets;
collaborate and support sales with their client development and acquisition strategies;
participate in the creation of unique content for presentations, sales or marketing needs as defined and prioritized by marcoms team in accordance with client requests;
collaborate with various internal teams including sales, scientific research & development, and design.

we want you to join us because you have:

proven interpersonal, collaborative and open communication skills;
excellent written and verbal skills in english, french, korean, japanese and/or mandarins;
capacity to synthesize complex information into easy to understand soundbites;
formal presentation skills;
extensive organization and planning skills;
creative problem-solver;
good judgement with an ability to make decisions when required;
team player with a positive attitude, not a lone ranger;
ability to handle ambiguity and proactively suggest actions to solve problems;
bachelor’s degree or equivalent professional qualification in science or business;
minimum of 3 years of relevant experience in market analytics, market research, category management, or consumer research;
minimum 2 years of experience in digital documentation management and concise knowledge distribution;
experience managing budgets (preference for client side not agency a bonus);
relevant product and industry knowledge (a bonus).

what we offer for your valuable work:

highly dynamic, innovative, passionate, entrepreneurial team;
open and inclusive company culture;
worldwide competitive salary; 
participation in the company success through the employee stock option plan;
participation in company employee benefits program;
flexible hours (outside of core hours);
autonomous, self-managed agile teams.

we strongly believe in collocated team dynamic. we would be happy to work with you if you can join the team in our montreal office.
we are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at our company. we do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status.







